## Middleware

### `RequestId`
Se aplica globalmente (primero en la cadena).
El `request_id` **siempre** lo genera el backend — nunca se lee del header del cliente.

```php
// app/Http/Middleware/RequestId.php
class RequestId
{
    public function handle(Request $request, Closure $next): Response
    {
        // Siempre generado por el backend — el header del cliente se ignora
        $requestId = (string) Str::uuid();

        Context::add('request_id', $requestId);

        $response = $next($request);

        // Propagado de vuelta al cliente para trazabilidad
        $response->headers->set('X-Request-ID', $requestId);

        return $response;
    }
}
```

El `request_id` se inyecta automáticamente en todos los logs vía `config/logging.php`:

```php
// app/Logging/InjectRequestIdProcessor.php
class InjectRequestIdProcessor
{
    public function __invoke($logger): void
    {
        $logger->pushProcessor(function ($record) {
            $record['extra']['request_id'] = Context::get('request_id');
            return $record;
        });
    }
}
```

### `AuthenticateJWT`
Verifica la firma del JWT y luego **hace lookup en DB** tanto del usuario como de la empresa.
No hay shortcut — un token bien firmado con un `user_id` inexistente o de un usuario eliminado debe ser rechazado.

```php
// app/Http/Middleware/AuthenticateJWT.php
namespace App\Http\Middleware;

use App\Domain\Auth\Exceptions\TokenExpiredException;
use App\Domain\Auth\Exceptions\UnauthorizedException;
use App\Models\User;
use Closure;
use Illuminate\Database\Eloquent\ModelNotFoundException;
use Illuminate\Http\Request;
use Illuminate\Support\Facades\Log;
use Symfony\Component\HttpFoundation\Response;
use Tymon\JWTAuth\Exceptions\JWTException;
use Tymon\JWTAuth\Facades\JWTAuth;

class AuthenticateJWT
{
    public function handle(Request $request, Closure $next): Response
    {
        try {
            // 1. Valida firma y extrae payload
            $payload = JWTAuth::parseToken()->getPayload();

            // 2. DB lookup del usuario — evita tokens con user_id fake o usuario eliminado
            $user = User::findOrFail($payload->get('sub'));

            // 3. Inyecta el usuario en el guard de Laravel
            auth()->setUser($user);

        } catch (TokenExpiredException) {
            Log::warning('auth.token_expired');
            throw new TokenExpiredException();

        } catch (JWTException) {
            Log::warning('auth.token_invalid');
            throw new UnauthorizedException();

        } catch (ModelNotFoundException) {
            Log::warning('auth.user_not_found', ['sub' => $payload->get('sub') ?? null]);
            throw new UnauthorizedException();  // mismo 401 — no revelar que el user no existe
        }

        return $next($request);
    }
}
```

### `SetActiveEnterprise`
Lee el header `X-Enterprise-ID` (hash), decodifica al ID numérico,
verifica que la empresa existe y que el usuario es miembro activo.

```php
// app/Http/Middleware/SetActiveEnterprise.php
namespace App\Http\Middleware;

use App\Domain\Enterprises\Exceptions\EnterpriseHeaderRequiredException;
use App\Domain\Enterprises\Exceptions\EnterpriseNotFoundException;
use App\Domain\Enterprises\Exceptions\EnterpriseNotMemberException;
use App\Models\Enterprise;
use App\Models\EnterpriseMember;
use App\Services\HashId;
use Closure;
use Illuminate\Database\Eloquent\ModelNotFoundException;
use Illuminate\Http\Request;
use Illuminate\Support\Facades\Log;
use Symfony\Component\HttpFoundation\Response;

class SetActiveEnterprise
{
    public function handle(Request $request, Closure $next): Response
    {
        $hashId = $request->header(config('app.enterprise_header'));  // X-Enterprise-ID

        if (!$hashId) {
            throw new EnterpriseHeaderRequiredException();  // 422
        }

        $enterpriseId = HashId::decode($hashId);

        if (!$enterpriseId) {
            throw new EnterpriseNotFoundException();  // 404
        }

        try {
            $enterprise = Enterprise::findOrFail($enterpriseId);
        } catch (ModelNotFoundException) {
            throw new EnterpriseNotFoundException();  // 404
        }

        // Verificar membresía activa
        $isMember = EnterpriseMember::where('enterprise_id', $enterprise->id)
            ->where('user_id', auth()->id())
            ->where('status', 'active')
            ->exists();

        if (!$isMember) {
            Log::warning('enterprise.not_member', [
                'enterprise_id' => $enterprise->id,
                'user_id'       => auth()->id(),
            ]);
            throw new EnterpriseNotMemberException();  // 403
        }

        $request->merge(['active_enterprise' => $enterprise]);

        return $next($request);
    }
}
```

| Caso | HTTP | Error code |
|---|---|---|
| Header ausente | 422 | `enterprise.header_required` |
| Hash inválido o enterprise no existe | 404 | `enterprise.not_found` |
| Usuario no es miembro activo | 403 | `enterprise.not_member` |

